  "texts": [
    "The 11th Five-Year Plan (2006-2010) marked an initial integration of ecological goals into a national strategy, culminating in the \"ecological civilization\" concept in 2012, which catalyzed a comprehensive green finance framework.",
    "Since then, China has emerged as a global leader in green finance, balancing economic growth with sustainability goals and supporting international climate initiatives, particularly through South-South cooperation.",
    "This historical perspective underscores the country's commitment to advancing sustainable finance and climate action on both domestic and international fronts.",
    "The examination of China's pathway to sustainable growth and its transformation through green finance, as seen in the five selected studies, reveals innovative financial mechanisms and strengthened environmental regulations that effectively channel capital toward sustainable development projects.",
    "Zhou et al. (2020) explored how green finance can simultaneously drive economic growth and environmental improvement across 30 Chinese provinces."
